). The $K$ band limit is consistent with $z>5$ from\nthe $K-z$ relation for radio galaxies, suggesting stellar mass limits using\nsimple stellar population models of $M_{\\textrm{stars}}< 10^{10.5}$ $M_\\odot$.\nIts high redshift coupled with relatively small radio and Ly$\\alpha$ sizes\nsuggest that TGSS1530 may be a radio galaxy in an early phase of its evolution.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 4 Jun 2018 16:37:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 10 Oct 2018 17:26:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-10-11"}
