ar arc,\ncircle, and outer planar graphs), and the class of incomparability graphs are\nstrongly transitive of the first type. For class of chordal graphs we give two\ndifferent proofs, using two different characterizations, verifying that they\nare co-strongly transitive of the first type. We present some containment\nresults.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 4 Jun 2018 20:44:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-06-06"}
