c) and the snowplough and Cioffi, McKee and Bertschinger\n(Astrophys. J. 1988, 334) results incorporating cooling and heating processes.\nWe show that our new timestep algorithm leads to linear rather than quadratic\nresolution dependence as the strength of the artificial viscosity varies,\nbecause of the corresponding change in the strength of interzone gradients.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 Jun 2018 09:19:38 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 14 May 2019 09:45:50 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 18 Jun 2019 06:33:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-15"}
