usive rates in the studied conditions,\nproducing an enhancement between 0.4 and 0.7 log units per 1 wt.% of added H2O.\nParticularly notable is the behaviour of the trivalent-only REEs (La to Nd and\nGd to Lu), with strong uphill diffusion minima, diminishing from light to heavy\nREEs. Modelling of REE profiles by a modified effective binary diffusion model\nindicates that activity gradients induced by the SiO2 concentration contrast\nare responsible for their development, inducing a transient partitioning of\nREEs towards the shoshonitic melt.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 Jun 2018 10:18:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-06-06"}
